{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"841e1f6b-1008-4c7e-a931-3b1b0a0f1681","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages:**\n   - Upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v4.6.0+** (you already have this ✅)\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n   - Add `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild`\n\n2. **Update your `.csproj`:**\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Add this property -->\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests with:**\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or directly via the built test host executable.\n\n**Key notes:**\n- NUnit3TestAdapter 4.6.0+ has built-in support for Microsoft.Testing.Platform — no extra NUnit adapter package is needed.\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` replaces `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` as the test host entry point.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses the new platform instead of VSTest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9317f770-b57f-4d90-ad15-606ab6a4c3ff","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question - I don't need to look at any specific codebase. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":349,"requestId":"0841:16A6CA:7F3D30A:8D6EC04:69EABE10"},"id":"ce1d145b-8d3f-4e51-93a2-734332dacb5d","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:49:28.380Z","parentId":"92c1bd51-a072-434b-89c1-4171f2024b1f"}
